description.narrative:
The overall objective of this contribution is to strengthen industrial relations and labour market conditions through social dialogue and well-functioning, credible labour dispute arbitration system. 
Moreover, three specific objectives under the overall objective that the intervention seeks to achieve are as follows:
1. To enhance effectiveness and accessibility of labour disputes resolution services in which the stakeholders have confidence;
2. To increase capacity of industrial relations stakeholders to participate in dispute prevention and resolution and social dialogue to effectively address their disputes;
3. To strengthen industrial integrity and sustainability of the Arbitration Council, Arbitration Council Foundation and their services. 
4. Specific objective (major amendment): To enhance effectiveness and accessibility of individual labour dispute resolution services in which the stakeholders have confidence.
